Rating: 4
Excellent! I interwove the par-cooked bacon with the chunks of swordfish and used chunks of roma tomatos. First, I tossed the tomato and fish in olive oil with 1/2 tsp minced garlic and a bit of pepper. Skewered and placed on BBQ grill for 3-4 minutes on each side. Turned off grill and let them sit for 5 min. I took reserve bacon grease and mixed with remains of marinade and 2 tsps melted butter. Heated that mix and poured over skewers and served. It was FABULOUS!!! Would be great served over pilaf or pasta. My 10 yr old gobbled it!

