Guests RAVED. they would probably say 4 forks! I made a few changes, added about 3 T of Flat leaf parsley and 1 t of lemon thyme, and the kosher salt a pepper and I made it for 6, so more garlic too (4 cloves). I did have to cook a lot longer than the 4 min a side, malybe close the grill cover and that would work?? I cooked the bacon about 4 min a side! ANd I also threaded the bacon like a ribbon around the swordfish. that really seamed to keep it moist. Was even good reheated! Not too many fish recipes can say that!

