Rating: 3
Thought this was a great *basic* recipe. I made it with halibut and used rosemary sprigs as skewers. Thinking that the bacon and rosemary would flavor it, I went against my instinct to throw on some kosher salt and pepper. Next time I will. I also used only four slices of bacon (I don't know what I would have done with more). I cut the bacon in 1 1/2 inch pieces. I guess if I had used the 8 strips, I would have cut them in much larger pieces so they would practically *wrap* around the fish. I'm excited to try it again with changes - it will be a summer regular. Served it with boiled new potatoes tossed in olive oil and rosemary, and a minted peach salad with brie.

Rating: 4
OH MY GOD, MY HUSBAND COOKED DINNER! This was fabulous, great pure flavors. It would be perfect for the midweek dinner party or for a large group. The bacon was cut into 1-2" pieces before being threaded and mushrooms were added. I could eat this once a week and its relatively low fat!

Rating: 4
If you like bacon, this recipe is excellent. The hardest part is frying the bacon to the right consistency, don't over do it. It will cook on the grill. Otherwise, very easy and very good.